final fantasy how can i raise money the quickiest away easy experience gil final fantasy while going through the nam yensa sandsea go to the northern most part of the sandscale bank you will encounter an enemy named bagolys they are worth to experience points each and can drop bent staffs which are worth approximately gil each fight them leave then come back repeat this as much as desired on the mission of the blue basilisk nidhogg one of the parts of the roads is a place where lots of skeletons keep appearing if they stop go off two maps then return the skeletons will respawn this requires a lot of patience but it will result in both experience points and gil because you get bone fragments and iron helms which sell for and gil respectively if you havent beat gil snapper at the track of the beast yet you could steal from him between g to g each time the problem is after each steal u have to run and quickly re zone and steal again with patience i managed to steal g from him take into account that he only appears during rainy season and theres heavy dark clouds in the sky also steal from the cactoid in the eastern sands you will steal a cactus fruit usually this sells for about or more gil each allowing you to get a decent amount of money to start the game once you can access the salikawood after the mosphoran highwaste in nabradia you can do this trick go north into the section of salikawood called quietened trace there should be a gate crystal save the game and switch to just one character this character should be able to equip the thief's cuffs accessory enter the grand bower section of salikawood the giant bomb optional boss will appear steal from it then exit the area heal at the crystal and repeat as much as desired the three items you can steal from him are bomb shell common which sell for about gil each fire crystal uncommon which sell for about gil each and the bomb fragment rare which sell for about gil each Children's television series Dragon Ball Pok__mon 